 likely diagnosis here?","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.34811,0.059141,0.059369,0.066571,0.064116,0.062062,0.057939,0.062682,0.061822,0.055916,0.058098,0.044174],"unified_progress":[0.22612,0.091401,0.070598,0.067379,0.078232,0.073105,0.087904,0.076831,0.071366,0.056618,0.051608,0.048837]},{"section":6,"text":"First, I remember that ovarian tumors can be germ cell tumors, cysts, or other types.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.095501,0.19853,0.064468,0.10345,0.088865,0.096135,0.073891,0.06693,0.060344,0.055708,0.050275,0.045896],"unified_progress":[0.097168,0.10696,0.066316,0.1015,0.093382,0.10776,0.084441,0.084369,0.078291,0.072185,0.061507,0.046121]},{"section":7,"text":"The presence of different tissues in the cyst wall is key.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.054149,0.10301,0.1194,0.11318,0.10376,0.09109,0.085765,0.076873,0.071937,0.069954,0.058074,0.052811],"unified_progress":[0.059309,0.08127,0.091504,0.10422,0.10122,0.096615,0.094126,0.089104,0.083837,0.080622,0.065457,0.052714]},{"section":8,"text":"Oh right, teratomas are germ cell tumors that can contain various tissue types because they arise from cells that can differentiate into any cell type.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044818,0.082491,0.094051,0.10276,0.10521,0.10155,0.097766,0.089269,0.080483,0.078085,0.064356,0.059156],"unified_progress":[0.050694,0.065884,0.085335,0.095234,0.099195,0.10966,0.10031,0.095788,0.089247,0.083555,0.068246,0.056849]},{"section":9,"text":"Wait, the term \"mature\" versus \"immature\" teratoma?","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048671,0.083,0.090463,0.096555,0.098944,0.09681,0.09522,0.090191,0.082982,0.083095,0.06941,0.064658],"unified_progress":[0.059391,0.068137,0.082912,0.092619,0.096729,0.10058,0.098121,0.095909,0.090019,0.085204,0.071614,0.058762]},{"section":10,"text":"Since the tissues here are benign (like skin, cartilage), that points to a mature teratoma.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048768,0.085444,0.09213,0.096413,0.096561,0.094525,0.093088,0.088397,0.083494,0.082114,0.070361,0.068705],"unified_progress":[0.054693,0.069425,0.083628,0.092908,0.096472,0.098647,0.096422,0.094403,0.090427,0.08482,0.073893,0.064261]},{"section":11,"text":"The mature cystic teratoma is the common type, often called a dermoid cyst.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039025,0.071849,0.082165,0.093099,0.099786,0.10042,0.10045,0.093531,0.086018,0.086672,0.072552,0.074433],"unified_progress":[0.042908,0.057749,0.078617,0.088801,0.0941,0.10595,0.10014,0.098266,0.094033,0.088844,0.078713,0.071878]},{"section":12,"text":"But dermoid cysts usually have skin elements, hair, glands.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03067,0.065097,0.078954,0.091431,0.10017,0.10325,0.10491,0.098594,0.091993,0.092301,0.0759,0.066728],"unified_progress":[0.042622,0.059435,0.078995,0.091117,0.097161,0.10497,0.10327,0.10155,0.096811,0.091341,0.074245,0.058486]},{"section":13,"text":"The black hair might be because the cyst has been there a long time, leading to pigmented hair.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042117,0.080154,0.085727,0.090826,0.094149,0.097579,0.097215,0.094159,0.091688,0.085367,0.074642,0.066377],"unified_progress":[0.050908,0.071647,0.084103,0.092596,0.097834,0.10001,0.097618,0.096123,0.093802,0.084117,0.072098,0.059141]},{"section":14,"text":"The cystic structure with sebaceous material fits because sebaceous glands are part of skin.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041309,0.079756,0.087744,0.093944,0.095599,0.097221,0.096719,0.09193,0.093969,0.082868,0.073126,0.065815],"unified_progress":[0.049105,0.071133,0.088053,0.097975,0.10282,0.10353,0.09974,0.094398,0.09313,0.079225,0.06605,0.054847]},{"section":15,"text":"The presence of brain tissue and mucinous epithelium is a bit unusual but possible in teratomas since they can have ectodermal, mesodermal, and endodermal derivatives.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033852,0.071688,0.084451,0.094327,0.099096,0.10113,0.10117,0.095196,0.092991,0.086457,0.074093,0.065548],"unified_progress":[0.037605,0.065325,0.085909,0.097367,0.10252,0.11071,0.10344,0.097608,0.094037,0.083133,0.067878,0.054468]},{"section":16,"text":"Brain is ectoderm, skin and glands are ectoderm too, cartilage is mesoderm, mucinous glands might be endoderm.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032742,0.069812,0.08254,0.092617,0.0983,0.1011,0.10197,0.096555,0.093971,0.087867,0.075761,0.066768],"unified_progress":[0.040767,0.064976,0.083477,0.095446,0.1012,0.10755,0.10271,0.098208,0.094488,0.084723,0.070093,0.056364]},{"section":17,"text":"So putting it all together: cystic, contains various tissues including skin with hair, benign components.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035115,0.068242,0.079139,0.086082,0.089809,0.091792,0.093856,0.092565,0.094849,0.093284,0.089172,0.086096],"unified_progress":[0.043393,0.060415,0.074005,0.084618,0.09168,0.096771,0.096687,0.096882,0.097494,0.09364,0.087629,0.076787]},{"section":18,"text":"That's a mature cystic teratoma, or dermoid cyst.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032958,0.058498,0.066343,0.075111,0.082225,0.086459,0.091041,0.091368,0.093728,0.09522,0.097671,0.12938],"unified_progress":[0.037995,0.044754,0.058009,0.068034,0.074085,0.085722,0.086857,0.093679,0.098805,0.10003,0.11552,0.13651]},{"section":19,"text":"The key differentiator from other tumors is the presence of these multiple differentiated tissues.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029443,0.061618,0.075395,0.082522,0.086073,0.087752,0.091535,0.092184,0.09483,0.098311,0.095553,0.10478],"unified_progress":[0.029987,0.050534,0.06285,0.074131,0.080068,0.087117,0.089905,0.096067,0.10114,0.10583,0.10954,0.11284]},{"section":20,"text":"Other options like endodermal sinus tumor (yolk sac tumor) would have different histology like schiller-duval bodies, but here it's all benign tissues.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026441,0.060135,0.074609,0.086185,0.094172,0.098427,0.10225,0.099827,0.097202,0.096095,0.086196,0.078467],"unified_progress":[0.027188,0.053685,0.071943,0.083602,0.092377,0.10108,0.10187,0.10346,0.10283,0.10108,0.088203,0.072694]},{"section":21,"text":"So yeah, the answer should be mature cystic teratoma.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023555,0.044581,0.053034,0.060891,0.069574,0.077178,0.084627,0.090072,0.098178,0.10113,0.11553,0.18165],"unified_progress":[0.02403,0.031328,0.039055,0.048977,0.054665,0.068004,0.071623,0.086138,0.096211,0.10759,0.15528,0.21711]}]}}